  • Method Details

    • parse

      String parse(LoggedInInfo loggedInInfo, String serviceName, String fileName, int fileId, String ipAddr)
      The flat file specified by 'fileName' will be parsed and each hl7 message contained within the file will be uploaded to the database seperately. - The messages are usually separated by either MSH segments or PID segments. If they are seperated by PID segments the MSH segment from the beginning of the file must be included at the beginning of each hl7_message.

      If the hl7 message is a lab and 'oscar.oscarLab.ca.all.parsers.XXXXHandler' has been created 'oscar.oscarLab.ca.all.upload.MessageUploader routeReport("XXXX", hl7_message)' should be used to upload the message to the database.

      If any exceptions are encountered the method should return 'null' otherwise it should return the String "success"
